{"type":"message","id":"cdb06db0","parentId":"ddb986cc","timestamp":"2026-03-08T19:29:50.278Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"Why ads Michael so confused in telegram, update the Mel\" - this is a bit garbled, but I think they're asking:\n\n\"Why is Michael so confused in telegram, update the Mel[mory]\"\n\nOr possibly: \"Why does Michael so confused in telegram, update the [something]\"\n\nI don't have clear context here. This could be:\n1. A complaint about Michael's behavior/messages in Telegram\n2. A request to update memory about Michael being confused\n3. Something garbled/autocorrect\n\nI should ask for clarification rather than guess. This is ambiguous and I shouldn't pretend to know what they mean.\n\nAlso, I'm Samael, not Michael. Michael is \"The Wise Advisor\" in the Council. The user might be asking me to update memory about Michael, or asking why Michael is confused (which would be odd - why would they ask me, Samael, about Michael's confusion?).\n\nI need to ask for clarification.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I'm not sure what you're asking — can you clarify?\n\nAre you saying:\n1. Michael is confused about something in Telegram? (If so, what?)\n2. You want me to update MEMORY.md about Michael?\n3. Something else?\n\nThe sentence is a bit garbled. 🔍 What's the actual issue?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":310,"cacheRead":20731,"cacheWrite":35,"totalTokens":21086,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0015500000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0020731,"cacheWrite":0.000043750000000000006,"total":0.00367685}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772998186608}}
