{"type":"message","id":"d2d6a710","parentId":"52ba3db4","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:15:41.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The emoji mapping might be hardcoded in the dashboard frontend or it might be derived from the SOUL.md metadata. Let me check if there's a dashboard HTML or JavaScript file that controls this. Or it could be in the workspace files themselves. Let me look for any file that might contain emoji → agent mappings.Actually, the simplest fix might be to check if the COUNCIL.md file is being used as a source for the dashboard display and update the emoji there if it's in the file. Let me look at the current COUNCIL.md file again — it doesn't have emojis in the table, just the archetypes.\n\nLet me search for where the emoji might be defined by looking at the souls files more carefully, or checking if there's a display metadata somewhere.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be simpler. The dashboard might be pulling the emoji from the agent ID or from a naming convention. Or it could be pulling from the first line of the SOUL.md file or from a dedicated manifest. Let me check if there's a visual descriptor in the SOUL files, particularly looking at Rafael's SOUL vs Michael's SOUL to see how they differ.\n\nRafael's SOUL.md ends with \"🕊️\" (dove)\nMichael's SOUL.md doesn't seem to have an emoji\n\nSo if the dashboard is auto-detecting the emoji based on the SOUL.md file, and if Michael's SOUL.md has the shield emoji and Rafael's doesn't, then maybe:\n1. Rafael's SOUL.md is missing the shield emoji and Michael's SOUL.md has it\n2. Or there's a mix-up in the files\n\nLet me search the actual SOUL files for the shield emoji.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_XeT9tpkjuSmMz7JvbURYs5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"🛡️\" /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-samael/souls/"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-202510