{"type":"message","id":"832481ae","parentId":"37b0e819","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:30:10.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking what model each agent is using. Let me check the config I already retrieved earlier.\n\nFrom the config:\n- Default model: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n- main: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n- rafael: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n- uriel: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n\n\n- gabriel: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n- raguel: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0\n- samael: no model specified (uses default)\n\nInteresting—my own runtime shows I'm actually running on Claude Opus 4.6, which is different from what the config specifies for these agents. They're all set to Haiku, but I'm operating on a different model.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"From the config I pulled earlier:\n\n| Agent | Model |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Samael** (me) | Claude **Opus 4.6** |\n| Rafael | Claude **Haiku 4.5** |\n| Uriel | Claude **Haiku 4.5** |\n| Gabriel | Claude **Haiku 4.5** |\n| Raguel | Claude **Haiku 4.5** |\n| Michael | Claude **Haiku 4.5** (default) |\n| Main | Claude **Haiku 4.5** |\n\n**Samael's flag:** 🚩\n\nI'm the only one on **Opus** (the heavy thinker). Everyone else is on **Haiku** (the fast, cheap, lightweight model).\n\n**What that means:**\n- Haiku is fast and cheap but **less capable** for complex reasoning\n- If Michael is hallucinating or Rafael is confused about identities, Haiku might be why\n- Opus costs ~10x more per token but thinks deeper\n\n**The question:** Is Haiku good enough for what they're doing? Or is the identity confusion you saw earlier a direct result of running the Council on the cheapest model?\n\nWorth considering. 🔍"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","